title: Grateful Dead Live at Civic Arena on 1989-04-03
description: Greatest Story Ever Told, Bertha, Walkin' Blues, Jack A Roe, El Paso, Built To Last, Victim Or The Crime, Just Like Tom Thumb's Blues, Don't Ease Me In Blow Away, Estimated Prophet-> Crazy Fingers-> Uncle John's Band-> Drums-> Jam-> Gimme Some Lovin'-> I Need A Miracle-> Stella Blue-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Johnny B. Goode, E: Black Muddy River

reviews.review_text:
Weir Ready This is all Wier for me.  I have been looking for a SBD of this show for 15 years.  The first night gets all the rave, and for good reason.  I however was partial to Bobby during this phase, it was just one of the zillion reasons that I was there.  The backhand, the antics,  name it.  Anyway during El Paso he had this shining blue light on him and it was just majestic.  Mydland's vocals are tight.  Now I am rambling.
Thanks for the Board!  I give it a 5 but I am not objective.

Nice Song Selection Very nice first set with a nice arrangement of Greatest Story>Bertha, JAR, El Paso, etc.  
Well played, solid throughout. Nothing spectacular, but we were fairly spoiled at this juncture.

In terms of wine vintages - Just short of a benchmark year.  Otherworldly fall tour leaves unforgettable finish.  96.

Pittsburgh 1989 I liked the first night better, but this is a nice show.  El Paso was a great surprise. Jerry blew the opening lyrics to Bertha, but got stronger the rest of the night. Good sbd here as well.

mellower This is a very different show than the 1st night - also a great show, but with a far more mellow, easy-going pace. Some interesting song choices and placements (Greatest Story opener!). Double encore is always nice too - good show!

4/3/1989 This show sounds amazing compared to the night previous. Pure Soundboard. Show fades in on GSET during the firest verse. Slight digital static sround 1 minute mark of GSET. 5 star sound, 3+ star performance-wise.

One of my funniest  show  stories.... I was comming from  NYC...Friend  was in  from  Germany  (army )...Went with 8 of  my  closest  friends....Made  with  major  driving  problems...got  lossed  a  few  times ..(no sleep - no  map-Etc...)So any who  we  were  ther  for the first  show  had  a  motel  room   ...My friend  Jerry after the  first night  ..couldnt  find  him  waited  for  what  seemed  like  hours...To no avail  went  back to the  motel  partyed...slept...Next  mornning  i  left  real early  hoping to find  ol jerry....Stopped at  a  pay  phone. wouldnt you  know  it  there  lay good  old  Jerry  curled  in  a  ball..Dead heads  any where  you need to lay  your  head  it  will be  so...  Grateful  TIMES ...lol  Peace
Solid show! Really good sound on this one. Worth repeated listening, so grab it from the server.
Jerry sounding nice Jerry sounds real cool at this show...this was the height of GD redux

Great Show Before Finals.. Super show...when should be been studying for
PITT finals.  Nearly broke up with boyfriend that
night....who is now my husband.  Never did like
the late '80s shows /  the Brent years.

Not as good as night before Overall: good show, but not quite as strong as night before, IMO.  Why is there a dearth of decent recordings of these Pitt shows?  Of the multiple recordings on Archive of these two nights, this is the only decent recording.   

The scene: after the disasters of the night before, this night had a cloud hanging over it.  Police state in PA.  I also remember hearing rumors that the band was really pissed off about the irresponsible behavior of people crashing the gates (duh, I was pretty pissed myself!).  Nonetheless, they came out and still played a great show.  

The music:  Not quite the heavy hitter of the night before, but still interesting song selections and good play.  El Paso was a bit of “break-out” as they hadn’t played it in quite some time.  The Phil chanters got a decent Tom Thumb’s.  Another second set Brent opener, with a ripping Blow Away.  Whole second set is fairly strong.  Brent is really prominent in these shows, which in my book is awesome, but some (crazy people!) don't agree.
BOBBY saw this one with CMU folk , IT WAS A TREAT!
april fools trip in was rough, 4 deaheads to one hockey fan, just want to say the band was awsome opening night  Brent spot on
